    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## LinkedIn PMP Question - Auto-Post Workflow\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n\nTRIGGER: Fires every Monday & Thursday at 7PM PKT (= 9AM New York / 2PM London)\n\nSTEP 1 - Get row(s) in sheet: Reads the latest question number from the Tracker tab so we always know where to continue from.\nSTEP 2 - Message a model: Asks Claude AI to generate a brand new PMP exam question and return it as structured JSON.\nSTEP 3 - Code in JavaScript: Adds +1 to the question number, formats the LinkedIn post text, and builds the answer comment text.\nSTEP 4 - Placid: Fills the image card template with the question data and returns a hosted image URL.\nSTEP 5 - HTTP Request: Downloads the Placid image as a binary file so LinkedIn can accept it as an upload.\nSTEP 6 - Create a post: Publishes the formatted question text and image card to LinkedIn as a public post.\nSTEP 7 - Update Row: Saves the new question number back to the Tracker tab so the next run increments correctly.\nSTEP 8 - Append Row: Logs the full question, options, answer, and explanation to Sheet1 as a future chatbot dataset.\nSTEP 9 - Wait: Pauses the workflow for 48 hours to maximise engagement before revealing the answer.\nSTEP 10 - HTTP Request: Posts the correct answer and explanation as a comment, re-activating the post in the LinkedIn feed.\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\nBuilt by PM Waqas | Channel: @PMWaqas",
        "height": 384,
        "width": 896
      },
